It happed once that a poor man came against him, and he having as then nothing ready to give and taking greater care of the poor naked than of his own body, took a gown and a hood both of like cloth which he had do make for himself to wear, and gave them to the said poor man and went home barehead. He held hospitality in- differently for the poor pilgrims in a house which he did make for the nonce, to the which he administered both meat and drink, bed and fire for to warm thern in winter.
